cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.DS 

This paper is about implementing a quantum cryptography protocol, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in the implementation. The implementation is done using programming languages, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and the paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) in the implementation.
